EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to workforce development; providing for the
creation of the Southern Nevada Health Care Workforce
Apprenticeship Pilot Program; making an appropriation;
and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides for the promotion, registration and approval of
2 apprenticeship programs in this State. (Chapter 610 of NRS) Section 1 of this bill
3 requires Workforce Connections to use the money appropriated by section 2 of this
4 bill to develop, create and administer the Southern Nevada Health Care Workforce
5 Apprenticeship Pilot Program for the purpose of addressing shortages in the
6 number of medical assistants and pharmaceutical technicians in this State through
7 the establishment of apprenticeship programs in Southern Nevada for the training
8 of such persons. Section 1 requires the Program to provide: (1) for the
9 establishment of apprenticeship programs in Southern Nevada for the training of
10 medical assistants and pharmaceutical technicians, which must be registered and
11 approved by the State Apprenticeship Council; and (2) money for participants in
12 the program to cover the costs of participating in the program, including, without
13 limitation, fees for professional certifications and registrations, as applicable, for
14 not more than 100 apprentices who are enrolled in apprenticeship programs
15 established under the Program.
16 Section 2 makes an appropriation to Workforce Connections to carry out the
17 Program.
