THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. Workforce Connections shall use the money
2 appropriated by section 2 of this act to develop, create and
3 administer the Southern Nevada Health Care Workforce
4 Apprenticeship Pilot Program for the purpose of addressing
5 shortages in the number of medical assistants and pharmaceutical
6 technicians in this State through the establishment of apprenticeship
7 programs for the training of such persons.
8 2. The Program must provide:
9 (a) For the establishment of apprenticeship programs in
10 Southern Nevada for the training of medical assistants and
11 pharmaceutical technicians. Any apprenticeship program established
12 under the Program must be registered and approved by the State
13 Apprenticeship Council pursuant to chapter 610 of NRS.
14 (b) Money for participants in the Program to cover the costs of
15 participating in the Program, including, without limitation, fees for
16 professional certifications and registrations, as applicable, for not
17 more than 100 apprentices who are enrolled in apprenticeship
18 programs established under the Program.
19 3. As used in this section:
20 (a) “Medical assistant” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS
21 630.0129 and 633.075.
22 (b) “Pharmaceutical technician” has the meaning ascribed to it
23 in NRS 639.0113.
24 Sec. 2. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
25 General Fund to Workforce Connections the sum of $300,000 to
26 carry out the Southern Nevada Health Care Workforce
27 Apprenticeship Pilot Program established pursuant to section 1 of
28 this act.
29 2. Any remaining balance of the appropriation made by
30 subsection 1 must not be committed for expenditure after June 30,
31 2027, by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
32 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
33 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
34 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
35 September 17, 2027, by either the entity to which the money was
36 appropriated or the entity to which the money was subsequently
37 granted or transferred, and must be reverted to the State General
38 Fund on or before September 17, 2027.
39 Sec. 3. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
